addcustomnumericformat.name: AddCustomNumericFormat
addcustomnumericformat.description:
Add a new numeric format to the document.  
The contents of the format string must be a valid format expression for Excel.
Consult Microsoft's documentation for rules for valid Excel format expressions.

addfont.name: AddFont
addfont.description:
Create a new font and add it to the document.
You can pass an existing font to copy its values into the new one.

addformat.name: AddFormat
addformat.description:
Create a new format and add it to the document.  
You can pass an existing format to copy its values into the new one.

addpicture.name: AddPicture
addpicture.description:
Add a new picture to the document from the file specified.
Formats supported include BMP, DIB, PNG, JPG and WMF 
Use the index value returned to reference the picture in other functions such as Office::Spreadsheet::SetPicture().

addsheet.name: AddSheet
addsheet.description: Add a new spreadsheet to the document assigning it the name provided.

addsheetfromdbf.name: AddSheetFromDBF
addsheetfromdbf.description:
Create a new spreadsheet and add it to the document.
Add the data in the table.
Optionally include headings, select a range of rows and include 
a SQL::TableInfo and user context to handle advanced transformations.

addsheetfromresultset.name: AddSheetFromResultSet
addsheetfromresultset.description:
Create a new spreadsheet and add it to the document.
Add the data in the result set.
Optionally include headings, select a range of rows and include 
a SQL::TableInfo and user context to handle advanced transformations.

clear.name: Clear
clear.description:
Reinitialize the Excel document as a new one.
Important Note: Be sure that you have saved any existing document data using Save or SaveToBlob() before calling this function.

copysheet.name: CopySheet
copysheet.description: Add a new spreadsheet to the document with the name specified by copying the contents of the sheet at index N.

customnumericformat.name: CustomNumericFormat
customnumericformat.description: Get the format expression for the custom numeric format at the index specified.

defaultfont.name: DefaultFont
defaultfont.description: Get the default font name and size for this workbook.

deletesheet.name: DeleteSheet
deletesheet.description: Delete the sheet at the index specified from the Excel document.

getfont.name: GetFont
getfont.description: Get the font indexed by Index.  Index must be a value between 1 and the number of fonts returned by the FontCount property.

getformat.name: GetFormat
getformat.description: Get the format indexed by Index.  Index must be a value between 1 and the number of formats returned by the FormatCount property.

getsheet.name: GetSheet
getsheet.description: Get the spreadsheet at the index specified.

load.name: Load
load.description: Load the contents of an existing Excel 2003 (.xls) file.

loadfromblob.name: LoadFromBlob
loadfromblob.description: Load the Excel Document from a memory image of an Excel 2003 (.xls) file.

newinstance.name: NewInstance
newinstance.description: Create a new object instance of the same type.

save.name: Save
save.description: Save the document to an Excel 2003 (.xls) file.

savetoblob.name: SaveToBlob
savetoblob.description: Save the document to a memory image of an Excel 2003 (.xls) file.

setactivesheet.name: SetActiveSheet
setactivesheet.description: Set the index of the spreadsheet that is considered active/current.

setdefaultfont.name: SetDefaultFont
setdefaultfont.description: Set a default font name and size for this workbook.

setlocale.name: SetLocale
setlocale.description: Set the locale name for the document.

tojson.name: ToJson
tojson.description: Returns all the Sheets in a spreadsheet as json.

getsheetnames.name: GetSheetNames
getsheetnames.description: Return a cr-lf delimited list of sheet names.

sheettojson.name: SheetToJson
sheettojson.description: Get a specific sheets cell values as JSON (first sheet if not specified).

sheetstojson.name: SheetsToJson
sheetstojson.description: Get all sheets cell values as JSON.

setlocale.description: Set the locale name for the document.

tojson.description: Returns all the Sheets in a spreadsheet as json.

cellformat.name: CellFormat
cellformat.description: Returns the format of a cell.  The format properties are updateable.

cellisdatevalue.name: CellIsDateValue
cellisdatevalue.description: Returns true if the cell is a date value.

celltype.name: CellType
celltype.description: Returns the enumerated type CellType indicating the contents of the cell.

clear.name: Clear
clear.description: Clear part or all of the spreadsheet.

clearprintrepeats.name: ClearPrintRepeats
clearprintrepeats.description: Clears repeated rows and columns on each page.

columnwidth.name: ColumnWidth
columnwidth.description: Returns the currently assigned width for a column.

copycell.name: CopyCell
copycell.description: Copy the cell and its format from SourceRow/Column to DestinationRow/Column.

getmerge.name: GetMerge
getmerge.description: Get the merged cell range that a particular cell belongs to.

getnamedrange.name: GetNamedRange
getnamedrange.description: Gets the range of rows and columns for a named range.

groupcolumns.name: GroupColumns
groupcolumns.description: Group FirstColumn through LastColumn.  If Collapsed is set to true the group of columns will be collapsed.

grouprows.name: GroupRows
grouprows.description: Group FirstRow through LastRow.  If Collapsed is set to true the group of rows will be collapsed.

insertcolumn.name: InsertColumn
insertcolumn.description: Insert new columns from FirstColumn to LastColumn.

insertrow.name: InsertRow
insertrow.description: Insert new rows from FirstRow to LastRow.

isblank.name: IsBlank
isblank.description: Returns true if a cell is blank. Assigns the current cell format to Format.

isformula.name: IsFormula
isformula.description: Returns true if the cell contains a formula.

read.name: Read
read.description:
Returns the data contents of a cell and updates Format with the cell's format.  
Note: Check the contents using CellType if the cell might contain an error.

readcomment.name: ReadComment
readcomment.description: Returns the text value of any comment assigned to the cell.

readerror.name: ReadError
readerror.description: Returns the error value, if any for a cell

readformula.name: ReadFormula
readformula.description: Returns the formula, if any, associated with the cell. Assigns the current cell format to Format.

rowheight.name: RowHeight
rowheight.description: Returns the currently assigned height for a row.

setblank.name: SetBlank
setblank.description: Sets the contents of a cell to a blank value and assigns a format.

setcolumn.name: SetColumn
setcolumn.description: Assigns a width and, optionally, a format for a column.  May also hide or show a column.

setformat.name: SetFormat
setformat.description: Set the format for a block of cells.

sethorizontalpagebreak.name: SetHorizontalPageBreak
sethorizontalpagebreak.description: Set a horizontal page break on the row specified.  Pass false to remove the break.

setmerge.name: SetMerge
setmerge.description: Merges cells from the first row and column through the last row and column specified.

setnamedrange.name: SetNamedRange
setnamedrange.description: Creates a named range for the rows and columns.

setpicture.name: SetPicture
setpicture.description:
Assign a picture to a cell using the identifier returned the function Office::ExcelDocument::AddPicture().
Scale the picture proportionally using 1.0 as full sized."

setprintrepeatcolumns.name: SetPrintRepeatColumns
setprintrepeatcolumns.description: Sets repeated columns on each page from FirstColumn to LastColumn.

setprintrepeatrows.name: SetPrintRepeatRows
setprintrepeatrows.description: Sets repeated rows on each page from FirstRow to LastRow.

setrow.name: SetRow
setrow.description: Assigns a height and, optionally, a format for a row.  May also hide or show a row.

setverticalpagebreak.name: SetVerticalPageBreak
setverticalpagebreak.description: Set a vertical page break on the column specified.  Pass false to remove the break.

split.name: Split
split.description: Split the sheet at the row and column specified.

tojson.name: ToJson
tojson.description: Return the cells as JSON array of objects using names in first column, or as array of arrays.

write.name: Write
write.description: Sets data value of a cell and assigns a format.

writecomment.name: WriteComment
writecomment.description: Assigns a comment and author to a cell giving it the designated text box size (in pixels).

writeformula.name: WriteFormula
writeformula.description: Assigns a formula to a cell and assigns a format.
